PEOPLE PLEASER??? Here’s 5 easy steps to effectively ask for what you want so you can create boundaries and have tough conversations in a way that will GET YOU HEARD!! 

This simple formula will help you craft a conversation that will empower you to ask for what you want and need, AND be heard. 

5 steps ……………………

1. Defuse defensiveness by acknowledging the other persons point of view or why you think they may have unintentionally done something to upset you or cross a boundary. TIP assume they didn’t MEAN have ill intentions. 

2. CLEARLY ask for what you want. If you need them to do multiple things say… “what I really need is for you to do these 3 things..” clearly state all three. 

3. Ask for acknowledgement “does that make sense?” “Does that seem fair and like something you’re able to do?”

4.  If they still seem to not be clear or understanding what you mean… explain why it matters to you, and how you’ll feel differently (or better) when they do the things you’re asking.

5. Ask what you can do for them in return. Be open to their feedback and if they have something they need from you be willing to hear them and if appropriate do what they are asking too, this way you both are able to move forward in a way that is clear and works for you both.

Confidence is built from 2 things… 

1. From what you tell yourself everyday. What does the voice in your head say you are worthy of? Capable of? Able to do? Ready to do? If that voice is tearing you down instead of building you up, it’s almost impossible to feel confident. The voice in your head MUST MATCH what you WANT to feel like. Note! I didn’t say match what you do feel like, but what you WISH/want to felt like. The voice creates the belief so it must always come first. It leads the way. So these mottos will help you guide that voice so the belief can come behind it. 

2. Confidence is built when the thing we’ve been telling ourself becomes our reality. In other words, when the results match the voice. 

So, if you want to build confidence in ANY AREA of your life, start with changing your internal voice on that topic, you’ll soon notice that you’ll begin manifesting that new result… and then it’s just a matter of rinse and repeat!!

It happens to all of us… and when I’m feeling “out of sorts,” frustrated, down or like I’m in a funk, these are the things I do RELIGIOUSLY to move out of it as quickly as possible and get back into the positive energy flow that will manifest my desired outcomes.

1️⃣ Guided meditations are the fastest way to change your energy. I love the ones on @youtube you can search for ome on any topic, I normally start with an “energy alignment” or cleanse. Do these twice a day for at least a week. It doesn’t need to be more then 10 min, but if I really need it, I’ll fall asleep to a longer one. 

2️⃣ use the tools in #thinkit (the 2nd step in my book #hustlebelievereceive ) to change those negative voices causing and enabling the funk. 

3️⃣ write a list of everything you control about the situation that is at the root of the funk. Remember you ALWAYS control at least 1 thing: what you chose to focus on. 

4️⃣ lastly, (and this is the key) write out your ideal dream outcome to whatever is bothering you. What if it all magically went RIGHT? How would that feel? What would be great about it? Then read that OFTEN and daydream about those moments going right. 

Bottom line… we manifest what we focus on… so if what you’ve been thinking of isn’t making your happy, you probably don’t wanna manifest it right? So changing that to what you DO WANT is critical, and these steps are how you practically do that.

Allow me to re-introduce myself 😁 Welcome everyone who’s new to my journey and for my OG’s thanks for supporting this ride ❤️

📚 10 years ago I was a blogger on a mission to PROVE that anything is possible for anyone, trying desperately to get my first book published.

I spent 3 years submitting quarry letters to agents and writing manuscripts, and 3 years getting rejection letters. 

Until a day in 2015 when I tried ONE MORE TIME, with one more idea, to one more agent. 

That lead to my first book deal for #hustlebelievereceive  in 2015. At the time I was a single mom (still am) living in an apartment with my 3 kids, and double hustling night and day, working a full time corporate job, coaching 100 people through my methods to beta test them, doing 50 interviews for the book and spending my nights writing it. 

Back then I never dreamed I’d have 3 #selfhelpbooks on the shelves at bookstores nationwide. 

I never dreamed I’d quit my job and do this full time. Never imagined I’d have started and run 2 businesses with no experience, knowledge or financial backing.

Never imagined my son would be living his dream playing football for the #oregonfootball 

Couldn’t have imagined I’d have 3 international retreats and take my kids to 7 countries. 

The list goes on… back then I had big dreams… but they weren’t this big! 

It’s been a journey fillled with big ups and big downs. Joy and pain. Struggle and growth. Lessons and adapting. Big wins and bigger losses. Failures, too many to name. Obstacles, more then anyone will ever know… 

BUT I did all this because I KNEW that if I could prove the impossible, possible for myself then maybe it would inspire YOU to believe you could do it too. 

That is still my mission every day. To share what I’ve learned so you are not living your life vicariously through anyone else, but inspiring others to live theirs through YOU.

Thank you for being part of my journey 🙏🏽❤️

Just a reminder that your life is happening TODAY… it’s not something that’s gonna magically get better, or be “perfect,” or slowdown, or whatever you’re waiting for… “someday.” It’s TODAY. 

It’s a choice to go in the playroom and get on the floor and play with your kids, because if they still want you too, that’s a tiny window in time and it’s a blessing you should try your hardest not to waste. 

It’s a choice to build traditions and meaningful routines and to prioritize making memories… rather than just letting today bleed into tomorrow. 

It’s a choice to take a beat and get your head together before you say that damaging thing that will scar the ones you love and that you can’t take back.

It’s a choice to see the beauty in the mess, the laughs in the chaos, the smiles after the tears. 

Your life is happening every day…. In all the small unrecognized and uncelebrated moments that no one sees… it’s not a magical destination… it’s a choice to open your arms to the daily ride. 

Enjoy all the moments… they really do fly by. ❤️❤️❤️

Are you going to choose to be in the moment today or spend the day stressing about some shit that hasn’t happened yet? 

Are you going to laugh out loud today, or keep that RBF? 

Are you going to reach out to that person in your life that you care about and tell them they matter to you… or are you gonna be self-absorbed?

Don’t wait for life to be “perfect” to show up in it BETTER… be better now and watch how your life improves.
